e, then assert all matching cache keys are invalidated and non-matching keys remain; include transaction commit timing case.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.76,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The eviction policy removes the correct entries — least-recently-used under LRU, least-frequently-used under LFU — when the cache is full.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"Core failure boundary is policy algorithm/state bookkeeping within cache structure (recency/frequency counters and tie-breaking). MOCK-MISS: no OS/network/subprocess or external dependency needed to reproduce wrong victim selection. REJECTION-GATE: rejected Integration because behavior text is about correctness of eviction decisions themselves, not inter-module signaling or infrastructure.","test_description":"Unit tests for eviction engine with deterministic access sequences: fill cache to capacity, apply reads/writes to shape recency/frequency, then insert one more item and assert exact key evicted under LRU and LFU (including tie cases).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.74,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
